<br>
The mare stopped and Hippolyte looked up in front of her.  There was a woman huddled against a tree crying.  The amazon slid off her mare and walked up slowely.  Her small hand not far from her dagger.  &quot;Are you alright?&quot;<br>
<br>
The woman looked up at her.  Eyes in fear as she tried to stand up, but was unable to.  &quot;Please please...don't hurt me!&quot;  The woman cried.<br>
<br>
The woman was not amazon...no.  Her clothes were very simple in fashion.  But, not greek.  &quot;Don't worry.. I won't hurt you.&quot;  Hipp caustiously glanced around looking for any danger.  But, she saw none.  Then her brown eyes traveled back down to the woman.  &quot;I am Hippolyte....I want to help you.  Tell me who did this to you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;My husband,&quot; the woman once again began to cry histerically.  <br>
<br>
Hippolyte's brow furrowed.  And then reached out to try and help the woman up.  &quot;Come...let's get you warm and something to eat.  I won't let anyone hurt you.&quot;<br>
<br>
The woman looked up thru tears for a bit and then slowely reached out..taking Hippolyte's hand.  Hipp smiled and gently helped the woman up, placing her arm underneath a bit to hold her up.  &quot;Let's get off the road first...these roads can be dangerous.&quot;  Slowely and carefully, she led the woman into the woods.  Her faithful mare following from behind. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

